com.complexible.stardog.api.versioning

Interface Version

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Ref

    public interface Version
extends Ref
    Metadata about a version. A version of the database is the set of triples contained in the database at one specific point. Each committed transaction automatically creates a new version.
    Since:
    2.2
    Version:
    2.2
    Author:
    Evren Sirin

      • getRelativeVersion

        Version getRelativeVersion(int theDistance)
                    throws StardogException
        Returns a version that is specified distance away from this version. Negative distance values return versions coming before this version and positive distances return versions coming after. If the distance references a version out of bounds, a null value is returned.
        Throws:
        StardogException

      • getTags

        List<String> getTags()
              throws StardogException

      • getDiff

        com.complexible.stardog.api.update.UpdateSequence getDiff()
                                                   throws StardogException
        Returns an update sequence that contains the statements added and/or removed in this version. Update sequence might contain 0, 1, or 2 update operations. Executing these update operations against the previous version of the database yields the statements contained in this version.
        Throws:
        StardogException
